examples.korean: For her to have survived such an ordeal was remarkable. 발음듣기 그녀가 그런 역경을 이겨낸 것은 놀라운 일이었다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary

examples.korean: There is not any memory with less satisfaction than the memory of some temptation we resisted. (James Branch Cabell) 발음듣기 우리가 이겨낸 유혹의 기억보다 더 만족스런 기억은 없다. (제임스 브랜치 캐벌, 경험명언) 명언/속담

examples.korean: The Indian climatologist who heads the panel, Rajendra K.Pachauri, said that the prize was proof that science had won out over skepticism. 발음듣기 이 위원회를 이끌고 있는, 인도의 기후학자인 Rajendra K.Pachauri는 이 상이, 과학이 회의론을 이겨낸 증거라고 말했다. Neungyule
examples.english: The Indian climatologist who heads the panel, Rajendra K.Pachauri, said that the prize was proof that science had won out over skepticism. 발음

examples.korean: From Dion’s humble French-Canadian beginnings to her husband’s recent bout with throat cancer to their joint victory over infertility, the couple has, it seems, always managed to overcome. 발음듣기 보잘것없던 디온의 신인 여가수 시절에서부터 최근 남편의 후두암 투병생활, 그리고 불임을 함께 이겨낸 성공 스토리에 이르기까지 이들 부부는 항상 용케도 역경을 극복해 온 것 같다. YBM All in All English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: From Dion’s humble French-Canadian beginnings to her husband’s recent bout with throat cancer to their joint victory over infertility, the couple has, it seems, always managed to overcome. 발음
